Description: The Bureau Of Justice Statistics is a source for criminal justice statistics.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: The Bureau Of Justice Statistics is a source for criminal justice statistics. It is a component of the Office of Justice Programs in the U.S. Department of Justice. The Bureau Of Justice Statistics’ mission is to collect, analyze, publish, and disseminate information about crime, criminal offenders, victims of crime, and the operation of justice systems at all levels of government. These data are critical to federal, state, and local policymakers in combating crime and ensuring that justice is both efficient and evenhanded. The Bureau of Justice Statistics was first established on December 27, 1979 under the Justice Systems Improvement Act of 1979, Public Law 96-157 (the 1979 Amendment to the Omnibus Crime Control and Safe Streets Act of 1968, Public Law 90-351).

Description: Real estate foreclosures and remodeling
Headquarters Regions: Midwestern US
Full Description: TravisJones, Rush Properties and Cherry Park Properties founder is a Johnson County, Kansas, businessman with expertise in real estate foreclosures and remodeling. Over the last 15 years, this experienced entrepreneur has assisted homeowners with their foreclosure needs by offering a diverse range of compensation options. As well, Travis Jones Rush Properties worked diligently to stimulate the Johnson County economic environment by increasing property values through responsible improvement projects. Currently, Travis Jones, Rush Properties founder, is a partner in Cherry Park Properties. Cherry Park Properties works with homeowners in both Kansas and Missouri to immediately purchase and improve distressed properties for resale. Using the experience gained by Travis Jones Rush Properties, properties are purchased in Kansas using Purchase of Redemption Rights. In Missouri, Travis Jones, Rush Properties founder can purchase properties at any point during the foreclosure process. By acting as both investor and property improvement coordinator, Travis Jones of Rush Properties has the ability to relieve homeowners of property that is cosmetically or structurally outdated and defective. Prior to Cherry Park Properties, Travis Jones and the Rush Properties team served extensively in volunteer positions throughout the local community. Travis Jones and Rush Properties also assisted many fundraising events including charity walks for the City Union Mission and the Church of the Resurrection. As well, Travis Jones of Rush Properties volunteered for local schools at concession stands, fund-raising carnivals and activity nights and served as a youth basketball coach. Outside of work, Travis Jones Rush Properties was involved in numerous charity golf tournaments and served at local homeless shelters and inner-city churches serving meals to the homeless. According to Travis Jones, Rush Properties also spearheaded the development of a community outreach project named Project James 2:17. This program was initiated to make a difference in the Johnson County, Kansas, community by offering financial assistance to people in need of a hand up. Travis Jones Rush Properties worked to provide rent-free housing to disadvantaged families for a period of 12 months. Travis Jones Rush Properties organization James 2:17 helped families make a positive change in their lives and transition into permanent homes. Travis Jones Rush Properties and James 2:17 partnered with area businesses to raise the needed funds to help pay for utilities, transportation, and food cost for tenants. Travis Jones Rush Properties became known throughout Kansas as a leader in the real estate industry. Through the two companies, Travis Jones, the Rush Properties and Cherry Park Properties founder, sought to provide a hassle-free experience for clients facing financial crisis. Today, Cherry Park Properties assists clients with various mortgage issues. Travis Jones of Rush Properties and Cherry Park Properties has been recognized as offering a superior alternative to foreclosure for homeowners. On a personal level, Travis Jones of Rush Properties and Cherry Park Properties enjoys gardening, landscaping, and boating with his wife and three children. TravisJones, Rush Properties and Cherry Park Properties founder, holds a Bachelor of Arts degree from Baker University. He additionally attended Kansas State University. Travis Jones of Rush Properties was a member of the Alpha Tau Omega fraternity.

That’s why Healthy Man Inc. was Founded and why products like The “Healthy Man Handbook” were created. It’s for all of us out there struggling to keep our body's healthy, both inside and out. We save them the time and resources they would be investing in recruiting, training, and paying an internal sales team by outsourcing the work to Titans of Tulsa. Full Description: Narian Technologies is considered one of the innovators in NFC or Near Field Communication Technology for over a decade.  It offers NFC Mobile Retail Services to Small, Mid-size, and Enterprise Level Retailers in 22 countries.  The offerings include a variety of Patented and Patent Pending NFC Technologies that allow real time interaction between consumer and retail employees, while in the retail location, as well as enhancing the customers shopping experience.  The core products are Narian Service, Narian Line, Narian Entrance, Narian Communicator, and Narian Media.  These core products design focus is human behavior and human interaction.  They address customer service needs in 16 unique retail market types including Restaurants, Clothing, Big Box, Grocery Supermarket, Pharmacy, Hotel Resort, and more.  As well as addressing the needs of 23 unique service markets including doctors offices, law firms, public transport, and more.   Currently available for commercial use in the United States, and limited commercial use outside the US, within select global markets including UK, France, Spain, Australia, Argentina, Korea, and more. Narian is mostly known for its retail services portfolio, but also has patented offerings including vending, medical prescription, and more.   Narian's additionally has consulting arm, that has advised companies ranging from start-ups to enterprise, on mobile technologies, NFC, business development, and revenue/product design and initiation within those areas.  Companies advised by Narian include 5th largest bank in the world, largest security company in the world, 2nd largest restaurant distributor in the world, second largest hotel resort chain in the world, two hedge funds, and many more. Narian as well, has initiated a grassroots movement known as NFC4ALL, and offers a Free Online NFC Application Creator, designed to allow the average person to create mashups of nearly two dozen advanced NFC Mobile Services.  The purpose of this movement is to generate excitement around new and unique ways for people to use NFC in their daily lives.
